# NEMETIC STRING
# Co_SPHERE_Framework (G019)
# Encoded: 2026-03-12
# Source: 25 - Co-SPHERE Framework.md

Φ(Co_SPHERE_Framework) = σ(coordination-distinction|action-vs-belief) ∘ ρ(pooling-resonance|plural-path-convergence) ∘ λ(dissonance-intensity|revision-pressure) ∘ β(affordance-growth|action-space-expansion) ∘ δγ(basin-ground|soft-coordination-substrate) ∘ μ(omega-permeability|structural-revisability) + ε | :open

# ── σ | Air | Aerunik ──
# σ(coordination-distinction|action-vs-belief) — emphasis 0.20
# The foundational distinction: Co-SPHERE coordinates action, not belief or identity.
# Air-element discernment that separates what participants do together from what they
# think or who they are. This distinction prevents the coordination basin from
# collapsing into consensus field, shared truth, or collective identity.

# ── ρ | Water | Sentaria ──
# ρ(pooling-resonance|plural-path-convergence) — emphasis 0.18
# Plural paths pool without fusion. Water-element resonance where different approaches,
# motivations, and perspectives converge into coordinated action without any party
# surrendering its distinct orientation. Pooling rather than merging.

# ── λ | Fire | Jvalion ──
# λ(dissonance-intensity|revision-pressure) — emphasis 0.14
# Dissonance is not threat but revision signal. Fire-element intensity that tests the
# basin's coherence and triggers omega-revision when coordination patterns no longer
# serve. In Co-SPHERE, dissonance is functional rather than pathological.

# ── β | Wood | Arboriel ──
# β(affordance-growth|action-space-expansion) — emphasis 0.16
# Collective coordination expands the space of possible action beyond what any
# individual participant could achieve alone. Wood-element growth of affordances
# through shared action — the basin generates possibilities that did not exist
# before coordination began.

# ── δγ | Earth | Humavita ──
# δγ(basin-ground|soft-coordination-substrate) — emphasis 0.14
# The soft basin as Earth-element ground: a coordination substrate that attracts and
# holds participants through utility rather than obligation. Not a sealed container
# but a gravitational well — easy to enter, easy to exit, functional while occupied.

# ── μ | Metal | Ferrosid ──
# μ(omega-permeability|structural-revisability) — emphasis 0.18
# Omega-permeability as Metal-element structural principle: the framework is revisable
# under dissonance. No coordination pattern achieves permanence; all structures remain
# open to revision when they cease to serve. Exit without punishment is guaranteed.

# Z-STATE: :open
# The system maintains openness as its primary state — neither sealed nor dissolved,
# neither permanent nor ephemeral. Open to entry, exit, revision, and dissonance
# without treating any of these as threats.

# TENDENCY: σ → 0.20
# Air-dominant tendency reflects the primacy of the action-vs-belief distinction —
# maintaining this discernment prevents Co-SPHERE from drifting into MemeGrid closure.
